WEBVTT

01:02.000 --> 01:07.370
Despondency breaks off its course.

01:07.430 --> 01:11.270
Anguish breaks off its course.

01:11.330 --> 01:16.930
The vulture breaks off its flight.

01:18.000 --> 01:22.270
The eager light streams out.

01:22.330 --> 01:26.100
Even the ghosts take a draft.

01:30.830 --> 01:34.230
And our paintings see daylight.

01:37.730 --> 01:41.970
Our red beasts of the ice age studios.

01:42.030 --> 01:44.720
Everything begins to look around.

01:44.770 --> 01:49.100
We walk in the sun in hundreds.

01:49.170 --> 01:54.200
Each man is a half-open door,
leading to a room for everyone.

02:06.230 --> 02:11.230
The water is shining among the trees.

02:11.300 --> 02:14.500
The lake is a window into the earth.

02:18.500 --> 02:24.870
♪ Tram wires cross northern skies ♪

02:24.930 --> 02:33.200
♪ Cut my blue heart in two ♪

02:33.270 --> 02:40.470
♪ My knuckles bleed down
the tattered street ♪

02:40.530 --> 02:47.870
♪ On a door that shouldn't
be in front of me ♪

02:55.430 --> 03:01.430
There's a noticeable difference.

03:01.500 --> 03:04.280
Because you're relatively young,

03:04.330 --> 03:06.420
because you're reasonably healthy,

03:06.470 --> 03:09.930
it is likely to take hold more quickly.

03:11.470 --> 03:12.920
How long?

03:12.970 --> 03:15.440
That's difficult to say.

03:18.700 --> 03:25.370
There will be moments of disorientation

03:25.430 --> 03:30.100
and possibly some more acute episodes.

03:30.170 --> 03:36.800
But it is time to start
making some adjustments, Kurt.

03:36.870 --> 03:40.330
It's time to tell people.

04:16.029 --> 04:20.829
Hi Linda, I spoke to...

04:20.899 --> 04:24.970
Linda, I spoke to the doctor, and, uh...

04:25.030 --> 04:26.680
I spoke to the doctor.

04:26.730 --> 04:28.020
I had to, um...

04:28.070 --> 04:31.600
I had to...

04:31.670 --> 04:34.900
I got a call from the, um...

04:37.200 --> 04:39.120
I had to speak...

04:39.170 --> 04:42.200
I wanted to just give you a chat...

05:41.750 --> 05:42.750
What is it?

05:42.800 --> 05:43.850
Have you got a minute?

05:43.900 --> 05:45.120
Yeah, yeah.

05:45.170 --> 05:46.840
Come on in.

05:47.550 --> 05:48.550
What's up?

05:48.600 --> 05:49.380
Um...

05:49.430 --> 05:50.380
Hang on.

05:50.430 --> 05:51.750
What's up, what's up?

05:51.800 --> 05:53.420
Hans's dad's gone missing.

05:53.470 --> 05:54.380
When?

05:54.430 --> 05:55.420
What happened?

05:55.470 --> 05:57.220
Sunday morning.

05:57.270 --> 05:59.880
Haåkon got up for his walk...

05:59.930 --> 06:01.750
... and left the house
before Louise got up.

06:01.800 --> 06:03.480
She heard him go, but he didn't come back.

06:03.530 --> 06:04.420
What time?

06:04.470 --> 06:05.280
6:00 a.m.

06:05.330 --> 06:06.280
He does it every day.

06:06.330 --> 06:07.320
And where does he walk?

06:07.370 --> 06:08.880
Sit down, sit down, come on.

06:08.930 --> 06:11.450
Past the lake, into the woods.

06:11.500 --> 06:13.250
The back of their place.

06:13.300 --> 06:15.880
It's a kilometer and a
half there and back.

06:15.930 --> 06:17.920
And has Louise told the police?

06:17.970 --> 06:19.180
Yeah, they've looked.

06:19.230 --> 06:23.130
I mean, I suppose whatever
the usual search is, but...

06:23.200 --> 06:25.120
Has Hans gone up?

06:25.170 --> 06:27.750
No, she told him not to drop
everything if he was busy,

06:27.800 --> 06:30.800
but he's upset, Dad, he's worried.

06:31.770 --> 06:33.720
Most people don't stay lost.

06:33.770 --> 06:37.130
90-odd percent of them
come back by themselves.

06:37.200 --> 06:39.530
Can you go up, Dad?

06:39.600 --> 06:41.680
See if you can help?

06:41.730 --> 06:43.230
Sure.

06:43.300 --> 06:45.050
Sure, I'll give Louise a call.

06:45.100 --> 06:46.250
Thanks.

06:46.300 --> 06:47.020
But I'm suspended, though.

06:47.070 --> 06:49.410
I can't arrest anyone.

06:53.930 --> 06:55.680
I'm sure it'll be fine.

06:55.730 --> 06:57.120
You tell Hans that.

06:57.170 --> 06:59.970
Tell him his dad will be fine.

07:03.600 --> 07:05.540
I love you, Dad.

07:10.770 --> 07:12.440
I love you.

07:16.530 --> 07:19.730
Why don't you go and pick up Klara?

07:19.800 --> 07:20.950
It'll be fine, sweetheart.

07:21.000 --> 07:22.480
Thank you.

07:22.530 --> 07:23.800
Bye.

08:18.680 --> 08:19.680
Oh, hello.

08:19.730 --> 08:20.680
Hello, Mr. Wallander.

08:20.730 --> 08:21.580
I can take your bag.

08:21.630 --> 08:22.520
Oh, I can...

08:22.570 --> 08:23.480
I can take it.

08:23.530 --> 08:24.320
Thanks.

08:24.370 --> 08:25.970
Thank you.

08:36.669 --> 08:38.070
Louise?

08:38.900 --> 08:41.100
Oh!

08:41.169 --> 08:43.270
Oh, Kurt.

08:43.330 --> 08:46.200
I thought it might have been...

08:46.670 --> 08:49.250
There's a policeman down over the lake.

08:49.300 --> 08:50.280
Ytterberg.

08:50.330 --> 08:53.530
I've told him you're coming.

08:53.600 --> 08:55.340
How are you?

08:55.970 --> 08:58.950
This is so kind of you, but really, I'm...

08:59.000 --> 09:02.770
Please don't worry about me.

09:04.430 --> 09:07.000
We'll find him, Louise.

09:09.370 --> 09:10.640
Yes.

09:13.530 --> 09:16.100
And no sign?

09:16.170 --> 09:17.450
Thanks.

09:17.500 --> 09:19.100
Wallander?

09:21.580 --> 09:22.580
Ytterberg.

09:22.630 --> 09:23.980
Good to meet you.

09:24.030 --> 09:26.500
They're calling it a day.

09:34.230 --> 09:37.080
The Navy sent a team to dredge the lake.

09:37.130 --> 09:38.580
He's not in the forest.

09:38.630 --> 09:40.380
The dogs couldn't find him.

09:40.430 --> 09:42.770
He's not in the water.

09:43.800 --> 09:47.130
His wife doesn't think he has any enemies.

09:47.200 --> 09:49.970
What do you think?

09:50.030 --> 09:51.630
Suicide?

09:51.700 --> 09:53.240
Accident?

09:56.800 --> 10:00.430
Be my guest if you want to look into it.

10:00.500 --> 10:02.820
We're not a big station.

10:02.870 --> 10:05.810
Another mind on this would be...

10:07.030 --> 10:09.570
Here's my card.

10:09.630 --> 10:12.330
Thanks, um...

10:12.380 --> 10:13.380
Sorry.

10:13.430 --> 10:15.020
Let me know if you find anything.

10:15.070 --> 10:17.170
Of course.

10:39.470 --> 10:41.520
You're fine, you're fine.

10:41.570 --> 10:43.310
You're 55...

10:44.700 --> 10:47.070
56...

10:47.130 --> 10:53.570
57, 58, 59, 60, 61.

10:55.300 --> 10:57.080
Come on, you're fine, you're fine.

10:57.130 --> 10:59.330
55, 56...

11:14.420 --> 11:15.420
Good morning, Louise.

11:15.470 --> 11:17.680
Are you a breakfast person?

11:17.730 --> 11:19.280
I'm diabetic.

11:19.330 --> 11:21.270
You're not fat.

11:23.200 --> 11:24.450
Well, I was wondering

11:24.500 --> 11:27.630
if Haåkon would have kept
the cards from his birthday.

11:27.680 --> 11:28.350
Does he usually do that?

11:28.400 --> 11:30.530
Oh, I doubt that.

11:30.600 --> 11:33.670
Now, what does a diabetic eat?

11:33.730 --> 11:36.620
Just some fruit, some cereal, or...

11:36.670 --> 11:37.680
Oh.

11:37.730 --> 11:39.820
You don't have to, it's fine, it's fine.

11:39.870 --> 11:42.010
Just help yourself.

11:42.170 --> 11:43.850
Haåkon's friend Sten called.

11:43.900 --> 11:45.320
He's waiting to hear from you.

11:45.370 --> 11:47.820
And, uh, there's his address.

11:47.870 --> 11:49.940
Okay, uh, sorry...

11:52.270 --> 11:55.570
Do you like Klara's kindergarten?

11:55.630 --> 11:58.470
Yeah, the teachers seem nice.

11:58.530 --> 12:00.850
Doesn't Linda want to stay at home?

12:00.900 --> 12:03.020
Or doesn't Hans earn enough?

12:03.070 --> 12:05.930
It's not a matter of, um...

12:08.500 --> 12:10.280
You know what, I'll
make this call, if I may.

12:10.330 --> 12:11.730
Thanks.

12:36.370 --> 12:37.970
Excuse me.

12:38.730 --> 12:40.280
Excuse me, Sten Norlander?

12:40.330 --> 12:42.570
Yeah.

12:42.630 --> 12:43.880
Wallander?

12:43.930 --> 12:45.550
Yeah, I think Louise
said to give you a call.

12:45.600 --> 12:47.320
Yeah, she did.

12:47.370 --> 12:48.320
Linda's dad.

12:48.370 --> 12:48.920
Right.

12:48.970 --> 12:50.320
Yeah, I can see it.

12:50.370 --> 12:52.450
Never met her, but...

12:52.500 --> 12:56.330
So, you weren't at
Haåkon's birthday party.

12:57.800 --> 12:59.550
My sister was sick.

12:59.600 --> 13:01.880
Plus it's not my kind of thing, so...

13:01.930 --> 13:04.180
Was there anything on his mind recently?

13:04.230 --> 13:07.500
Anything troubling him?

13:07.570 --> 13:10.080
Would you say he was depressed?

13:10.130 --> 13:11.080
Yeah.

13:11.130 --> 13:14.130
Like about 60% of the population.

13:15.900 --> 13:18.500
I mean, he was a brooder.

13:18.570 --> 13:21.150
All this stuff just lately --

13:21.200 --> 13:24.970
Putin sending subs into Swedish waters,

13:25.030 --> 13:27.380
whether or not we should do anything,

13:27.430 --> 13:32.100
whether or not we identify
them, provoke an incident.

13:32.170 --> 13:34.720
It'll have brought it all back again.

13:34.770 --> 13:37.680
The submarine incursions from the '80s?

13:37.730 --> 13:40.520
Pretty much torpedoed the both of us.

13:40.570 --> 13:41.250
You think somebody's killed him?

13:41.300 --> 13:44.900
Why would somebody kill him?

13:44.970 --> 13:47.430
They wouldn't.

13:47.500 --> 13:50.370
He didn't kill himself, though.

13:51.900 --> 13:53.550
You want to come out?

13:53.600 --> 13:56.370
No, thank you.

14:02.900 --> 14:07.530
Can you remember the last
thing that he said to you?

14:07.600 --> 14:09.800
I don't know.

14:09.870 --> 14:12.380
Probably something about boats.

14:12.430 --> 14:15.830
Not much else to talk about.

14:15.900 --> 14:20.600
I don't think either of us
have ever done much else.

14:51.430 --> 14:52.550
Wallander.

14:52.600 --> 14:53.720
Hi Kurt, it's Lennart.

14:53.770 --> 14:55.520
Are you all ready for tomorrow?

14:55.570 --> 14:57.270
Sorry?

14:57.330 --> 15:00.200
The internal affairs interview.

15:00.270 --> 15:01.480
Uh, yeah.

15:01.530 --> 15:02.480
Yeah, no, fine.

15:02.530 --> 15:03.680
You'll be there, right?

15:03.730 --> 15:05.020
Yeah, 10:00 a.m., Kurt.

15:05.070 --> 15:06.680
All right, okay.

15:06.730 --> 15:07.780
I'll see you tomorrow.

15:07.830 --> 15:09.100
Okay.

15:09.800 --> 15:11.050
Bugger.

15:11.100 --> 15:13.500
Bugger, bugger, bugger.

15:22.530 --> 15:24.600
10:00 a.m.

