Did you discuss the submarine incursions?

16:23.500 --> 16:24.850
The idea that the government

16:24.900 --> 16:28.400
had purposely let the
Russian submarines go?

16:28.470 --> 16:31.830
They did purposely let them go.

16:31.900 --> 16:33.250
We were out on the archipelago.

16:33.300 --> 16:34.520
We were scrambled.

16:34.570 --> 16:35.750
You know this.

16:35.800 --> 16:37.420
It was all on the news.

16:37.470 --> 16:39.250
It went all the way to the prime minister.

16:39.300 --> 16:41.420
You think the prime minister...

16:41.470 --> 16:43.120
I thought...

16:43.170 --> 16:44.420
I'm so sorry.

16:44.470 --> 16:46.900
I just found a...

16:46.970 --> 16:48.470
Sorry.

16:50.630 --> 16:55.370
Do you know where he
used to play billiards?

16:55.430 --> 16:57.970
He doesn't play billiards.

16:59.370 --> 17:01.320
Just it's the only other
thing in the diary.

17:01.370 --> 17:03.500
He doesn't play.

17:03.570 --> 17:05.770
He's dead, isn't he?

17:06.530 --> 17:09.400
What the hell's been the point?

17:13.470 --> 17:14.480
Louise?

17:14.530 --> 17:16.530
Good night, Kurt.

17:45.630 --> 17:47.480
Why don't you call Hans and Linda, or...?

17:47.530 --> 17:48.950
I'm a sailor's wife.

17:49.000 --> 17:51.520
I'm used to being on my own.

17:51.570 --> 17:54.930
Louise, you don't have to
go through this by yourself.

17:54.980 --> 17:55.680
I'll get them to come up.

17:55.730 --> 17:57.380
I have friends.

17:57.430 --> 17:59.300
I'm all right.

18:01.670 --> 18:03.020
Goodbye, Kurt.

18:03.070 --> 18:05.010
Goodbye, Louise.

